cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.MM

The paper deals with the topic of adversarial attacks on automatic speech recognition systems, which falls under the broad category of computer security (cs.CR). Specifically, the paper focuses on the robustness of these attacks in an over-the-air scenario, which involves signal processing and communication aspects (cs.SD, cs.SY). The paper also employs techniques from natural language processing and audio signal processing (cs.CL) and uses a room-impulse-response simulator to harden the adversarial examples against varying room characteristics (cs.MM).
